'''Sven Ove Hansson''' (born 1951) is a professor of [[philosophy]] and chair of the Department of Philosophy and History of Technology at the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] (KTH) in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. He is an author and [[Scientific skepticism|scientific skeptic]], with a special interest in environmental [[risk assessment]], as well as in [[decision theory]] and [[belief revision]].<ref name="Gärdenfors2011">{{cite journal|last1=Gärdenfors|first1=Peter|title=Notes on the history of ideas behind AGM|journal=[[Journal of Philosophical Logic]]|volume=40|issue=2|year=2011|pages=115–20|doi=10.1007/s10992-011-9174-6}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last= Yamin |first= Tughral |year= 2012 |title= An appreciation of the Pakistani Military thought process |journal= Strategic Studies |volume= 32 |issue= 2-3 |url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/1313161381? |via= [[ProQuest]] |accessdate= 2014-05-09 |subscription= yes}}</ref>

==Career==
Hansson obtained a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[Medicine|medical science]] in 1972, and then worked for a Swedish [[trade union]], followed by a job with the Swedish [[Swedish Social Democratic Party|Social Democrats]].
He received a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] in [[theoretical philosophy]] at [[Uppsala University]] in 1991, following which he was from 1993 to 1999 forskarassistent (the Swedish equivalent of an associate professor) at Uppsala. He received a second PhD in [[practical philosophy]] at the [[University of Lund]] in 1999, and since 2000 he has been a professor at KTH; he became department head in 2005.<ref name="cv">{{cite web |url= http://home.abe.kth.se/~soh/sohcv.htm |title= CV for Sven Ove Hansson |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130917235512/http://home.abe.kth.se/~soh/sohcv.htm |archivedate= 2013-09-17 |website= home.abe.kth.se |deadurl= no |publisher= [[Royal Institute of Technology]] (KTH) |location= Stockholm}}</ref>

The [[Government of Sweden|Swedish Government]] appointed Hansson to the Products Control Board (1976–1982; the predecessor of the National Chemicals Inspectorate), the National Board for Spent Nuclear Fuel (1981–1992) and the Natural Science Foundation (1989–1992). He continues to write on radiation exposure risk assessment.<ref name="Radiation protection">{{cite journal|last1=Hansson|first1=Sven Ove|title=Radiation protection—Sorting out the arguments|journal=Philosophy & Technology|volume=24|issue=3|year=2011|pages=363–8|doi=10.1007/s13347-011-0036-5}}</ref> He was also a member of two temporary Commissions on environmental policies appointed by the Swedish Government, expert advisor to a 1999–2000 Swedish government committee the ''kemikaliekommittén'', and a member of the board of the MISTRA project New Strategy for the risk management of chemical substances. Hansson's contributions on theories of risk assessment have been cited as recently as 2012.<ref name="Rossi2012">{{cite journal|last1=Rossi|first1=John|title=The prospects for objectivity in risk assessment|journal=[[Journal of Value Inquiry]]|volume=46|issue=2|year=2012|pages=237–53|doi=10.1007/s10790-012-9338-9}}</ref>

Since December 2000, Hansson has been a member of ''forskningsberedningen'', the Swedish government’s advisory board of researchers.

Hansson has contributed to the development of [[belief revision]] theory, in particular, analysis of application of [[Belief revision#The AGM postulates|the AGM postulates]].<ref name="Gärdenfors2011"/><ref name="RottPagnucco1999">{{cite journal|last1=Rott|first1=Hans|last2=Pagnucco|first2=Maurice|title=Severe withdrawal (and recovery)|journal=[[Journal of Philosophical Logic]]|volume=28|issue=5|year=1999|pages=501–47|doi=10.1023/A:1004344003217}}</ref> His work is also cited in discussions of [[ethics]] in institutional [[decision-making]].<ref name= "Fischer 2008">{{cite journal |last= Fischer |first= Robert |date= 30 December 2008 |title= European governance still technocratic? New modes of governance for food safety regulation in the European Union |journal= European Integration Online Papers |volume= 12 |pages= 1–26 |url= http://search.proquest.com/docview/231320612? |via= [[ProQuest]] |accessdate= 2014-05-09 |subscription= yes}}</ref><ref name= "Arcuri 2007">{{cite journal |last= Arcuri |first= Alessandra |year= 2007 |title= Reconstructing precaution, deconstructing misconceptions |journal= [[Ethics & International Affairs (journal)|Ethics & International Affairs]] |volume= 21|issue=3 |pages= 359–79,275 |url= http://search.proquest.com/docview/200527747 |via= [[ProQuest]] |accessdate= 2014-05-09 |subscription= yes |doi=10.1111/j.1747-7093.2007.00104.x}}</ref> [[Google Scholar]] lists 6,244 citations of his work and gives his [[h-index|''h''-index]] as 42 and [[i10-index]] as 133.<ref name= "G Scholar">{{cite web |url= https://scholar.google.com/citations?sortby=pubdate&hl=en&user=unbqCy0AAAAJ&view_op=list_works |title= Sven Ove Hansson |accessdate= 2014-05-09 |work= [[Google Scholar]]}}</ref> {{as of|2014}} he continues to publish on ethics, [[logic]] and [[public health]] in major journals.<ref name= "G Scholar"/>

Since September 1999 he has been the Editor-in-Chief of ''[[Theoria (philosophy journal)|Theoria]]'', the only international, peer-reviewed, philosophy journal published in Sweden. He was the founding chairperson of the [[Föreningen Vetenskap och Folkbildning|Swedish Skeptics]] (Vetenskap och Folkbildning),<ref name= "Prof Para">{{cite news |last1= Jerkert |first1= Jesper |first2= Sven Ove |last2= Hansson |title= A Swedish professorship in parapsychology |magazine= [[Skeptical Inquirer]] |date= July–August 2006 |volume= 30 |issue= 4 |page= 8 |via= [[ProQuest]] |url= http://search.proquest.com/docview/219293316? |subscription= yes |accessdate= 2014-05-09}}</ref> and is still a board member and editor of the organisation’s journal ''Folkvett''.

Hansson has criticized [[anthroposophy]] as a [[pseudo science]].<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.waldorfcritics.org/active/articles/Hansson.html |title= Is anthroposophy science? |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20020420035401/http://waldorfcritics.org/active/articles/Hansson.html |archivedate= 2002-04-20 |magazine= Conceptus XXV |year= 1991 |issue= 64 |pages= 37–49 |via= waldorfcritics.org |last= Hansson |first= Sven Ove}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://skepticreport.com/sr/?p=480 |title= The racial teachings of Rudolf Steiner |magazine= Skeptic Report |date= 1 June 2005 |last= Hansson |first= Sven Ove}} According to the original publication of the article in Swedish (Folkvett nr 3/2004.), it was written in response to criticism of the Swedish branch of the CSICOP for its publication the previous year of a critical anthology on anthroposophy as being repeatedly unreliable.</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1= Dugan |first1= Dan |first2= Judy |last2= Daar |title= Are Rudolf Steiner's Waldorf schools 'non-sectarian?' |magazine= [[Free Inquiry]] |year= 1994 |accessdate= 2014-05-09 |via= [[HighBeam Research]] |url= http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-15349553.html |subscription= yes}}</ref>

==Publications==
He has published numerous articles and books in Swedish and in English.

