'''Welleran Poltarnees''' is the [[pen name]] of '''Harold Darling''',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.librarything.com/author/poltarneeswelleran|title=Welleran Poltarnees - LibraryThing|publisher=|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schoollibraryjournal.com/slj/printissue/currentissue/886240-427/professional_reading.html.csp|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328111723/http://www.schoollibraryjournal.com/slj/printissue/currentissue/886240-427/professional_reading.html.csp|dead-url=yes|archive-date=28 March 2012|title=That Page Was Not Found - School Library Journal|publisher=|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> an [[author]] who is best known for having written numerous "blessing books"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jacketflap.com/persondetail.asp?person=15916|title=Beth Shade - Books, Biography, Contact Information|publisher=|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> that employ turn of the 20th century artwork. This pen name is based on two of [[Edward Plunkett, 18th Baron Dunsany|Lord Dunsany's]] most famous stories: ''The Sword of Welleran'' and ''Poltarnees, Beholder of Ocean''.
